Placeholder for Map Help

Map Basics:
    - New Map: Add tab with default 48x24 grid.
    - Openings: 7-digit code (0-4) for edges (top-left to bottom-right clockwise + center); 0=none, 1=open, 2=door, 3=unit (rope/hole/ladder), 4=non-interactive door.
    - Width/Height: Set dimensions (0-1080); apply to resize (preserves data, fills with space).
    - Type: Safe, Crawl, Fight, Mix0, Mix1, Mix2, Mix3, Mixed.
    - Name: Map title (max 28 characters).
    - Maker: Creator name (max 21 characters).
    - System: Auto-set to "PB [no-jam] PyEditor".

Symbol Placement:
    - Select Symbol: From list (e.g., ' '=Walk Space, '#'=Wall); place with left-click.
    - Select Mode: Use -- to enter select mode for properties or multi-select.
    - Right-Click: Remove symbol (set to space) or select cell.
    - Multi-Select: Drag in select mode; apply edits to region.
    - Lock Apply: Lock properties to auto-apply on matching symbols.

Properties:
    - Color: Text color (e.g., white, red).
    - Texture: String for visual effect.
    - Name: Custom name.
    - Value: Integer (0+).
    - Depth: Integer (1+).
    - Height: Integer (1+).
    - 3D Effect: Checkbox for depth simulation.
    - Apply: Set to selected cell/region; clear specific or all via menu.

Edit Operations:
    - Copy/Cut/Paste: On selected region.
    - Replace: Change symbols in region to current.
    - Make New Map: Create tab from selected region.
    - Generate New Section: Auto-generate extension (TODO).
    - Clear Selected Properties: Reset props in region.
    - Remove Selected: Clear symbols and props.
    - Undo/Redo: For grid changes.

Arcs Integration:
    - Attached Arcs: Shown as green dots below grid; right-click dot to load arc.
    - Load Arc to Map: Attach loaded arc.
    - Save All from Map: Export attached arcs.

File Operations:
    - Save as .tmap: Single map with header, grid, footer, props, arcs.
    - Save as .mapd: Dictionary with import header and loose arcs; exports maps as separate .tmap.
    - Load .tmap/.txt: Single map.
    - Load .mapd: Multiple maps via import, plus arcs.

Door Connections:
    - Use openings code and symbols (+=Door, -=Non-Interactive Door, L=Ladder, H=Hole, R=Rope).
    - Follow Door Transversal Guide for valid exit->entrance patterns.

